window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>I'm his muse. His addiction.</b></p> <p>Rian Merrick is a wildly talented tattoo artist, the unhinged \"rockstar\" professor on campus. Everyone's obsession.</p> <p>Now, I'm his.</p> <p>He doesn't care that I'm his student. He won't stop til I belong to him and he's ruined me.</p> <p>I'm trying to resist him—Lord knows, I'm trying—but my body screams for him. Why do I ache for him even though I know it's wrong? How can something that feels like Heaven be a sin?</p> <p>He thought I was his redemption.</p> <p>Instead, he will be my damnation.</p> <p>He's a broken man with a dark price to pay—a price I can't pay again. When his demons come for him, can I let him go before he drowns us both?</p> <p>Dark Ink<i> is a dark, angsty romance dealing with addiction and toxic relationships. If you don't like your heroes over-the-top and obsessive, and you don't like your spice \"degrading\" and \"impactful\", walk away. Otherwise, strap yourself in and grab onto your \"oh shit\" handle, this is a roller-coaster that won't stop til the bittersweet end...</i></p> <p>Dark Ink <i>is a standalone novel with a HEA.</i></p>"; 
